Roll bread dough into 1/2-inch-thick rectangle on lightly floured surface; brush with oil. Cut into 1-inch pieces, using sharp knife; place in large bowl. Add cheese, salad dressing mix and bacon; toss to coat. Place on ungreased baking sheet; shape into oval loaf. Let rise in warm place until doubled in volume. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Bake loaf 20 to 30 min. or until golden brown. Remove from pan to wire rack to cool.